        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40316",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dancet",
                        "name": "dancet",
                        "displayName": "Bart Dens",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a quite big issue, need to implement a REST client for one of my clients, and they require a specific enctype to be set.\r\n\r\nHowever, the above issue blocks me from implementing it with Zend_Rest_Client as the setRawData function call now clears my previously set enctype through self::getHttpClient()->setEncType('MY_ENCTYPE')",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dancet",
                        "name": "dancet",
                        "displayName": "Bart Dens",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-30T01:35:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-30T01:35:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49537",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=httpete",
                        "name": "httpete",
                        "displayName": "Pete Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Bart, you are right. We just fought like maniacs here trying to figure out why it wouldn't work, and patching Zend_Rest_Client as patched above worked first shot. Thanks but please fix in the core framework in 1.11.12.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=httpete",
                        "name": "httpete",
                        "displayName": "Pete Smith",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-19T21:31:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-19T21:31:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50440",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gfaust",
                        "name": "gfaust",
                        "displayName": "Guido Faust",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Wouldn't it be better to change Zend_Http_Client's setRawData() ?\r\n\r\nWe don't need to overwrite the EncType there if it is NULL!\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n{noformat}\r\n\/**\r\n     * Set the raw (already encoded) POST data.\r\n     *\r\n     * This function is here for two reasons:\r\n     * 1. For advanced user who would like to set their own data, already encoded\r\n     * 2. For backwards compatibilty: If someone uses the old post($data) method.\r\n     *    this method will be used to set the encoded data.\r\n     *\r\n     * $data can also be stream (such as file) from which the data will be read.\r\n     *\r\n     * @param string|resource $data\r\n     * @param string $enctype\r\n     * @return Zend_Http_Client\r\n     *\/\r\n    public function setRawData($data, $enctype = null)\r\n    {\r\n        $this->raw_post_data = $data;\r\n        if (!is_null($enctype)) {\r\n            $this->setEncType($enctype);\r\n        }\r\n        if (is_resource($data)) {\r\n            \/\/ We've got stream data\r\n            $stat = @fstat($data);\r\n            if($stat) {\r\n                $this->setHeaders(self::CONTENT_LENGTH, $stat['size']);\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        return $this;\r\n    }\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gfaust",
                        "name": "gfaust",
                        "displayName": "Guido Faust",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-04T08:06:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-04T08:06:37.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
